Dev Setup:
1. Pip install - https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/installing/
2. Clone the project from - https://github.inbcu.com/newsroom-systems/synthetics
3. Setup virtual environment (optional)
4. Install depended Python modules using the requirements.txt file
    1. Navigate to application folder, make sure requirements.txt file exists
    2. Run - pip install -r requirements.txt
    3. Check installed packages - pip list
5. Run the Synthetics script under 'feature' folder - behave -n â€˜Login NEAT'

Note - Make sure you are not in NBC(NBC_CORP) network while pip installing the packages.


Python - Virtual Environment
Setup
* Check if pip package virtualenv is installed.
* pip install virtualenv to install virtualenv package.
* virtualenv <name of virtual env> to create a virtualenv.
example - virtualenv transitalert_env
* source virtualenv/bin/activate to activate the virtualenv created above.
Activate and Deactivate virtualenv.

Activate - source <virtualenv_name>/bin/activate
Deactivate - deactivate
